    "description": "Every sailor on Odysseus's ship could tie a knot in the dark, in a storm, with wet hands. You will learn five knots — and you will know not just how to tie each one, but why. The square knot binds two ropes together. The bowline makes a loop that will not slip. The clove hitch holds fast to a post. The figure-eight stops a rope from pulling through. The sheet bend joins a thin rope to a thick one. Five knots, five purposes. Tie them wrong and the whole thing falls apart. Tie them right and they hold the world together.",
    "what_to_build": "A knot display board — a piece of driftwood or a small wooden plank with all five knots tied and labeled, mounted for display.",
