    "description": "Long before Odysseus sailed, the earth was writing its own story in stone. You will learn to read it. Eight rocks and fossils — granite, limestone, obsidian, sandstone, quartz, a trilobite, a fern impression, an ammonite — and you will know each one by sight and touch. More than that: you will know how it was made. Was it squeezed by heat? Layered by water? Shot from a volcano? Sedimentary, igneous, metamorphic — three words that unlock the history of every stone you will ever pick up. Most people walk past rocks. You will pick them up and tell their story.",
