    "kid_instructions": "\"You're going to learn eight rocks and fossils — not just their names, but how the earth made them. Fire, water, pressure — every rock has a story. You'll hold them, sort them, and build your own collection. When you test, you'll name them all and tell me how each one was born. Miss one and you study it again.\"",
    "pass_criteria": "Correctly identify all 8 specimens by name, classify each as sedimentary, igneous, or metamorphic, and give a one-sentence explanation of how each formed.",
    "counselor_notes": "Sandstone vs. limestone is the hardest distinction for this age — have the kid practice the scratch test and acid-drop test (vinegar on limestone fizzes) before testing."
