    "description": "The ancient cartographers drew the world from memory — coastlines, rivers, borders — because they had traveled it, studied it, committed it to mind. You will not draw the whole world. But you will master fifteen countries: find each one on a blank map with no labels, no colors, no hints — just outlines. And for each country you point to, you will name its capital. Paris, Tokyo, Nairobi, Brasília, Canberra. Fifteen nations, fifteen capitals, placed precisely on the unmarked globe. Most adults cannot do this. You will be able to do it by the end of the week.",
