      "Step 2 — Add three more pieces (Bach's Toccata and Fugue, Tchaikovsky's Nutcracker March, Grieg's In the Hall of the Mountain King). Log each. Quiz yourself on all six by hearing just the first 15 seconds.",
      "Step 3 — Add the final four pieces (Dvořák's New World Symphony, Debussy's Clair de Lune, Rossini's William Tell Overture, Strauss's Blue Danube). Log each and self-test on all ten.",
      "Step 4 — Shuffle practice: have a friend play random 10-second clips. Name the composer. Drill any pieces you miss until you can identify them from the opening bars.",
