    "kid_instructions": "\"Ten famous pieces of classical music. You'll listen to each one until you know it in your bones — then when I play just the first few seconds, you tell me who wrote it. Beethoven, Mozart, Vivaldi — they're all in there. This takes a few weeks of real listening. Don't rush it. Come test when you're sure.\"",
    "pass_criteria": "Correctly identify the composer of 10 of 10 classical pieces from 10-second audio clips played in random order.",
    "counselor_notes": "Beethoven's 5th and Bach's Toccata are easy — Debussy's Clair de Lune and Dvořák's New World are where kids stumble. Make sure they listen to these extra."
