    "kid_instructions": "\"One sheet of paper. You fold a plane that flies for five seconds and hits a target fifteen feet away. Sounds easy — it's not. You'll build a bunch of planes that fail before you find the one that works. Fold it clean, throw it smooth. When you're ready, you fold your plane in front of me and fly it twice: once for time, once for accuracy.\"",
    "pass_criteria": "Fold a paper airplane from a single sheet. Flight 1: stay airborne for 5+ seconds. Flight 2: hit a 3-foot-diameter target from 15 feet. Both criteria must be met (may be separate throws).",
    "counselor_notes": "Wind ruins this quest — test indoors or on a dead-calm day. If the kid can consistently hit 4 seconds but not 5, check their release angle (too high = stall, too low = nosedive)."
