    "description": "The Vikings carved Elder Futhark into stone. The telegraph operators tapped Morse through copper wire. The Greeks gave the Western world its alphabet. You will master one of these ancient or secret scripts — not just learn a few letters, but write fluently. By summer's end you will compose full sentences, encode messages your friends cannot read, and decode messages written to you. This is the deepest literacy quest at camp: a full summer of practice, one symbol at a time, until a second alphabet lives in your hand as naturally as the first. Choose your script. Commit. Write it until it is yours.",
